# Architecture layers (`src/`)

## Folder map

| Layer | Path | Responsibility |
|--------|------|----------------|
| App | `src/app/` | Providers, global store, routing only. No UI components, no feature business logic. |
| Pages | `src/pages/` | Route-level composition only. Compose features into layouts. |
| Features | `src/features/` | Business logic, feature UI, API/socket per feature. |
| Entities | `src/entities/` | Domain models and types. **Pure TypeScript** — no React, no hooks. |
| Shared | `src/shared/` | Reusable UI, hooks, lib, constants. **Generic** — must not depend on features. |

## Import matrix

| From → To | app | pages | features | entities | shared |
|-------------|-----|-------|----------|----------|--------|
| **pages** | ✓ | internal | ✓ | — | ✓ |
| **features** | — | — | internal only | ✓ | ✓ |
| **shared** | — | — | **✗** | ✓ (types only if needed) | internal |
| **entities** | **✗** | **✗** | **✗** | internal | **✗** |

**Forbidden:** `features/*` importing another `features/*` directly. **Forbidden:** `shared/*` importing `features/*`.

## Examples

```tsx
// BAD — page calls API
// pages/ChatPage.tsx
const data = await fetch('/api/chat'); // never

// GOOD — page only composes feature entry
// pages/ChatPage.tsx
import { ChatWelcomeSection } from '@/features/chat/components/ChatWelcomeSection';
export function ChatPage() {
  return <ChatWelcomeSection />;
}
```

Use path alias `@/` → `src/` if configured; otherwise use relative imports consistent with the repo.
